result.name: Xihe Yayuan

reviews.text: Price is OK for the location and interior design.  Food taste ok. Frankly the Peking Duck is quite fancy but all I want is traditional one.  Worst thing is once the big glass door to the open area opened, the whole area become very hot, it made the chopsticks the wood table very humid and sticky. And the big glass door is kept opening closing opening closing ........

The Peking duck was amazing, I never knew there were 3 ways to eat it. If you are up for something different, I would highly recommend it.
We also ordered other dishes, the Sichuan fish was on point with spice levels.
Customer service was above average and welcoming.
Only issue it's at the very end of the pier but you do get water views.

Nice and authentic Beijing Cuisine. All the dishes that we tried are really tasty and yummy. The Staffs are also polite and friendly. You should give it a try if you are walking around the Harbour City.

The Peking duck is actually pretty good despite what some of the reviews say. The skin is very crisp. Most of the dishes are quite good. The only drawback is they are served too fast, all at the same time. Service and attitude is not bad either. The menu also contains dishes tailored for HK people, which is different from what I had in Beijing.
Nice food and reasonable price.
